<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Another thing to remember....</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Angus[CC]">Angus[CC]</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 12:17 p.m. 26/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Another thing to remember....<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1959" TARGET=_self>Re: Druids vs. Wizards</A> (Seoman Snowlock[CC-Council])
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>After level 30 Druids experience a rather severe power down. While wizards are just scratching the surface of damage spells. Soon the mana Vs damage of a wizard is just to much to handle. Keep in mind though that this really doesn't happen till around level 34 with spells like Ice shock and Thunderclap, and then at 39 with spells like Lightning Strike and Immobilize. These spells are extremely mana efficent much more so than the druid spells at that level. This is wear wizards will come out on top. But before 30 a wizard doesn't have a chance against a competent druid 1v1. Actually, any healer for that matter. Spells are not efficent for us to beat out the heals, but I do know a few tricks with stun spells that can really screw them up to the point that they could lose. But again a good player knows what to do. I have casted on a druid who did nothing but heal and had them within one spell of death, and it basicly would have been a race to see who got the next spell off first.

<P>Overall before level 30ish-34 it's just stupid to duel a Druid. avoid it like the plague.
<P>&gt; Well...in most duels with a wizard you won't have time to cast a
<BR>&gt; DoT on him until he is out of mana (unless you opt to cast it as
<BR>&gt; your first spell which increases the chances that his offense
<BR>&gt; will overtake your heals later). You won't me using your mana
<BR>&gt; offensively anyways so why pretend :P Heal up as he unloads on
<BR>&gt; you and if you do it right, the wizard will run out of mana
<BR>&gt; without getting you below 2 bubbles of hp and you will even have
<BR>&gt; some mana left over for a couple of swarms as you crack his
<BR>&gt; skull with your club :P
<P>&gt; Seo
<BR>&gt; ps: it takes a smart wizard to have any chance vs a healer, it
<BR>&gt; takes a semi-competent healer to beat ANY wizard :P
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
